Package <Unnamed>

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Main
    Regex2NFA is the driver class for the REGEX Engine It will open a file a text file that contains postfix order Regular Expressions separated one per line, and then create an NFA for each of these REGEX Main will use the first command-line parameter as the name of the file to open.
    NFA
    This class defines the NFA object an NFA is comprised of a 5-tuple of values {Q,S,D,q0,F} These values are as follows Q: The set of all states in the NFA (represented as a linked list of states) S: The language of the NFA (For our purposes, this will always be {a,b,c,d,e,E,} (E represents the empty string) Checking that inputs are within the language will be handled by the method passing parameters to this constructor D: The transitions between states.
    State
    This class defines an Object of type State.
